properties.Name: EquifaxCompanyNonFinancialPaymentCreditExperiencesAndStatus
properties.Description: A summary of non-financial payment credit experiences and status by industry.

Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX IDâ„¢ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description:
Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded
by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: EquifaxFinancialAccountStatusTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Financial Account Status Type.

Columns.Name: DateReported
Columns.Description: Date Reported refers to the most recent data submission received from the contributing data source;

Columns.Name: BalanceAmount
Columns.Description: Total reported balance including any past due amount.

Columns.Name: TotalPastDueAmount
Columns.Description: Total amount past due from each aging category.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory1
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 1 period. Most creditors view Category 1 as 1-30 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory2
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 2 period. Most creditors view Category 2 as 31-60 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory3
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 3 period. Most creditors view Category 3 as 61-90 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory4
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 4 period. Most creditors view Category 4 as 91-120 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory5
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 5 period. Most creditors view Category 5 as 120+ days past due.

Columns.Name: DateOfFirstDelinquency
Columns.Description: The date of the first delinquency.
